        <abstract>
            <p>On success of THH’s Edinburgh lectures.</p> 
<p>Agrees that THH is right that the hybrid question is a "hiatus" [in the argument for natural selection] but he overrates it. Crossed <hi rend="italic">varieties</hi> frequently produce sterile offspring. On this question asks THH to read his <hi rend="italic">Primula</hi> paper [<hi rend="italic">Collected papers</hi> 2: 45–63]. CD suspects sterility will come to be viewed as a <hi rend="italic">selected</hi> character.</p> 
        </abstract>
